oops introduction

Oops is a micro architecture framework written in javascript.
It has no dependencies to other frameworks and works on a very
balanced level to enlarge support on several devices.

The main focus of oops is to provide a solid object orientated
framework which implements common design patterns. Its all about
loose coupling and structuring your code.

Core Pattern

Observer Pattern
Factory Method Pattern
Composite Pattern
Trait Pattern
State Pattern
Proxy Pattern
represents adapter, mediator or decorator
Core Features

inheritance and polymorphism
type-safe objects
protected scope
internal scope
super statement
packages
prevent namespace conflicts
interferences with objects that shares the same name